The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sachin named best batsman
                                                                                                                       7                                      Sachin named best batsman
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Sachin Tendulkar, the Mumbai Indians captain, was named best batsman while the Deccan Chargers Pragyan Ojha bagged the best bowler honour at a glitzy IPL Awards Night here Friday.         
	Sachin, who turns 37 on Saturday, has 570 runs in his kitty from 14 matches with five fifties. Sachin was also named best batsman and best captain in the Viewers Choice category.         
	Among Sourav Gangulys Knights, David Hussey won the Viewers Choice Award for the best catch, while Brendon McCullum won the best breakthrough performance award for 2008.         
	The Awards Night was boycotted by the BCCI brass.         
	Jury Awards         
	Best batsman: Sachin Tendulkar (MI); Best bowler: Pragyan Ojha (DC); Best debut performance: Kieron Pollard (MI); Best dramatic performance: Harbhajan Singh (MI); Most consistent performer: Jacques Kallis (RCB); Best breakthrough performance 2008: Brendon McCullum (KKR); Best breakthrough performance 2009: Anil Kumble (RCB); Best fielder: AB de Villiers (DD); Best ground: M Chinnaswamy Stadium, Bangalore; Best stadium experience: DY Patil Stadium, Navi Mumbai.         
	Viewers Choice Awards         
	Best catch: David Hussey (KKR); Best batsman: Sachin Tendulkar (MI); Best captain: Sachin Tendulkar (MI); Best bowler: Pragyan Ojha (DC); Best commentator: Ravi Shastri; Most stylish player: Robin Uthappa (RCB); Most fan-friendly cricketer: Adam Gilchrist (DC); Best fielder: Suresh Raina (CSK).         
	Statistical Awards         
	Most economical bowler: Ravichandran Ashwin (CSK); Fastest hundred: Yusuf Pathan (RR); Highest percentage of runs scored in boundaries: Virender Sehwag (DD)         
	IPL Captains Award         
	Indian cricketing legend I would want in my team: Kapil Dev.                                                                                                                     
